Kamehachi is my favorite neighborhood spot! This is a three generation woman-owned business that serves our Old Town neighborhood. Amazing food and great service!

We got great service, they have Japanese whiskey and smart cocktails, and the sushi was thoughtful. The flavors in the other food were a little off, though (neither authentic nor quite balanced, in our opinion), the cocktails were a little watery, and the lava cake didn't flow. I wasn't disappointed in the meal, but I'm not in a hurry to go back.

This is an amazing place, I love the ambiance here. I come to this location for a very quiet lunch during the weekdays snd sometimes  for dinner with friends, it does get very busy on weekends so you always want to make reservations. Their wait staff and bartenders are really nice. The spicy tuna deluxe deluxe and summer are amazing, I recommend those rolls if you ever vist.
Great food, drinks and service. I loved their Tuna poke and the spicy edamame. I will be back for sure!
Hosts and waitstaff were extremely helpful and pleasant. Food was delicious and cocktails were tasty and strong. Wonderful atmosphere, not extremely loud. Great place for a date.
Great food the sushi is amazing and they have good drinks I'll definitely return again.
Great service and delicious!

If you’re looking for nice dinning restaurant this place is not for you. Very loud, not clean, tables are shaking, servers are not welcoming. They just want you to eat, pay and go quickly as possible. Sushi rolls was not as we ordered. Definitely not my recommendation.

1st time here, had not that great time here. I lot of people screaming around, definitely not a place for nice dining with friends. Rolls are ok but nothing special. We ordered a couple different rolls some with good torched salmon. But at the and everything came without any change like we ordered.
Really beautiful space.  Food was really good. The steak was ok but everything else made up for it.
Great food , very good service

With a business that has been around since 1967, they must be doing something right! The fish is the freshest I’ve had so far in the city and the sushi rice for me is most important and they do it perfectly. They even have black rice and brown rice options for each roll!!!
4 star restaurant, bonus star for being the oldest Japanese in the Windy City.  10/10 would recommend.

(Translated by Google) A pleasant space and one of the few open in this time of pandemic. The food is good, but very scarce, the prices are a little higher than the normal range. You know the service is great when you don’t notice the server and the drinks don’t stop coming through. I asked for a sushi recommendation and got back a bliss of salmon, cilantro and jalapeño. Covid stuff is handled well.
Japanese cuisine. Nice location.

Awesome waitstaff. Yord was amazing. He deserves a promotion. Very attentive and very quick service. Food was solid, not the best I’ve ever had but I loved the ambiance and the service so 5 stars for sure.

Quite confused by all the high ratings and praise. Perhaps its down to the dishes.  Went with one more person, we ordered 5-6 dishes total.  Best thing I had was the yellowtail starter. Advertised as lemony and salty, but just garlicy and super sweet. Corn syrup adjacent.  The standout awfulness was the Chutoro which looked like "chewed toro" it was absolutely inedible and looked like glued together sinew. 3 slivers of the rankest least appetizing tuna, 10$ each. I have had fatty tuna before, don't you gaslight me, reader.  Overpriced. Weird flavor combinations. _REALLY_ leaning into that salt and garlic. I don't get the hype. Possibly I got unlucky given the ratings, give it a go if youre in the neighb.
No, really not! Quite expensive, very plain taste, nothing extraordinary... We wanted to test something new. We did it once. We won't do it again.
Much better sushi nearby. I haven't tried other dishes, but I tried three different rolls and they severely lacked flavor.

I am not coming back because I am from Asia and I know the average quality of the food. I mean service is good. Gyoza.. taste like factory frozen gyoza. Does not look fresh at all and the server spilled soy sauce so I took it back. It was not worth penny. Fish.. it was very fishy. They said they are getting fresh fish every day. So it maybe fresh but it didn’t cook properly. Also look at the portion.. it didn’t fill me up at all. I am so disappointed.
Solid dependable sushi. I'd consider mid-tier type quality.

Probably the best takeout sushi you can get in old town/Gold Coast area. Consistently gotten it and tried everything around, and they have NEVER let me down. Will continue to order from here exclusively!
4.0 stars for their sushi
Amazing atmosphere, incredible food. Great place for a date night. Services is amazing.
Amazing sushi

Very well organised and welcoming restaurant. They provide generous portions and for inexpensive prices. We loved the meals very much and the staff were very personal and chatty. Recommended.
Not that tasty

Love this place.
One of the best places in Chicago to get sushi. Great atmosphere/decor. Friendly staff. Sushi is on point. Drinks are really good too. You won't be disappointed.
We love seeing BATSU here. Upstairs menu is limited but tasty. Downstairs in the restaurant proper, menu selections are incredible.
The food was good, service ok.. the cook were not Japanese....

Definitely a good hole in the wall spot for sashimi! I would recommend going at least an hour early to wait in line that way you can get it first round for seats. The fish was super fresh and and the price is definitely worth it. I definitely recommend checking it out if you're in the little tokyo area
Great Atmosphere, wonderful host, server was terrible,  sushi was just “ok”. Not a good value.  All in all, we won’t be back.

Came here around 9:35p waited until 10:03p with no service except for a glass of water. This firm should really work on communication and should realize that if a customer has been sitting idly for 20 + minutes they should checkup on them.  I addressed the manager and he apologized. Mistakes happen and hopefully they can improve down the road

Ordered the Tokobushi (red abalone) & Otoro (fatty bluefin tuna) nigiri and the Summer, Blazing red dragon (definitely the best one, great red chili sauce) & Crouching tuna, hidden crab rolls.  I've had similar roll combinations and offerings of similar quality at equal or cheaper prices elsewhere. Friendly staff but there are other places I can go for similar fare.

Overall has quiet ambience! Relaxed and dim lights will set the mood in dinners. But foods are little over-priced! Our dishes came out as imperfect, didn’t get enough choices for replacements! Not quite good if food is important for your outing, may be you will enjoy company of your wonderful partner or group only!
The food was good but we were not well treated which we can only assume was because we arrived in late-ish. We arrived in at least 30 minutes before the last seating according to the website though.
Come here for the lamb chops and hot food. Really amazing lamb chop dish. Rolls and sashimi we're very good but not great. Service was extremely good.
Service was great, food was alright. Nothing to write home about. Average and overpriced food but the service was wonderful.
Good quality fish, nice presentation, and very good service.

The place was really nice. The food was really great. but apparently the reason why we didn't get the best service that we expect it was because they were super busy and the sushi bar was backed up. Seems to me that perhaps they are understaffed.  Besides the slow service everything else is great!
By far the best sushi in Chicago.
Consistent
Some of the best sushi in Chicago.

I have gone to kamehachi weekly for years. The food and specials were excellent. Now with a new chef things have changed. Don't like the new specials and miss the delicious items thatvare now gone. Won't be back.

We came here on Saturday night. We ordered crab cake and oysters. Oysters was awaful. Crab cake was mixed with mayonnaise or something..weird taste.. with half of crab immigration meat. Very cheap made for the price. Next we had few rolls. I thought rolls would be better than appetizers, nope! They were dry and didn’t taste good. Didn’t like food here and not coming back

We made a last minute reservation and they were happy to accomodate us. The food was great, but the service...not so much. Being so close to Second City and Zanies you'd think they would know how to get people in and out in time for a show, but instead we had to wait an insufferable amount of time to order our food, which I will admit did come rather quickly. But instead of taking our order, we and the table next to us got to watch the waitress chat it up with regulars and no other servers seemed one bit interested in helping, nor did the manager | host.
Good sushi at high prices

We were a little underwhelmed by the food. It's a great place to for light bites of scrumptious sushi and cocktails. However it was not the best for people that are not fans of seafood. The atmosphere is low lit and the wait staff is attentive.
Sashimi Zen was a great choice. Totally worth it. Fish is so fresh. The Tuna sashimi and Uni nigiri are amazing. You get a decent amount of fish from the Chicago Crazy Roll
Reasonably priced fresh sushi. The Udon was a little bit salty though
Sushi did not taste fresh and the choices were limited & unusual. Martinis were also not the best tasting

Went to go watch Batsu with friends for a birthday. The show is hilarious, the sake was smooth, and we had a great time. Highly recommend this show for anyone who wants to have a good time, just check any expectations at the door.

My boyfriend and I both left here feeling slighted from the food we were served. To start, our service was slow to begin with. It tasted good, but for $71 bill we feel that we should have received more sushi when ordering the $34 sushi combo. Did our waitress bring out the right plate? We ate it because we hadn't ate all day and we were starving. I'm including pictures. We left still hungry and with a lukewarm feeling.
Overpriced and underportioned food. The fish is extremely browned for what they call “fresh”.

Came in at 11:30am and sat at the bar. Only waitress/bartender, Aurora, was nice. She gave me a dinner menu and a "Today's nigiri" menu. I picked an udon bowl and a red snapper nigiri. Five minutes later the other customer at the bar gets her order delivered. I asked what's that? and Aurora says that's a bento box from the lunch menu.  Well I didn't get a chance to order from the lunch menu. The udon was fine but I really would have liked a bento box. Might come back if in the area again.
Ambiance to burn! Nabeyaki Udon was fine but nothing compared to Akai Hana, Wilmette. Get their recipe. Be more generous with portion size.
Tiny portions...
Always good...
It was a pleasant atmosphere
Aesthetically pleasing interior designs. Delicious food. Spot on service especially our waitress who was superbly nice!
Beautiful atmosphere, great service, delicious sake and sushi. We had the two sake flights, spicy tuna and salmon deluxe rolls and everything was amazing. Great quality fish!
Always good food. Service can be hit or miss. Good wine and beer selections

Excellent !!!

Amazing sushi, atmosphere, and service. At first glance, it might just seem like an upscale bar. However, when you walk further into the restaurant, you encounter a cozy, relatively large dining room. The sushi menu is not the longest, but you will be highly satisfied with what is listed. The specials were delicious as well!

(Translated by Google) Not for the small budget but with excellent quality and very good service.  Nice and modern atmosphere, delicious drinks and excellent sushi.  (Original) Nichts für den kleinen Geldbeutel aber mit hervorragender Qualität und sehr gutem Service.  Schönes und modernes Ambiente, leckere Getränke und hervorragendes Sushi.

OMG. Best experience eating sushi and drinking sake I've ever had in my life. This is one of Chicago's oldest sushi bars, but everything about was modern and vibey. Our group had VIP tickets to the Batsu show on the second floor so the whole night was packed with laughter and great food.   Check this place out!
Food is really good and the place is great for conversations with friends and family.
Excellent food and service.

Modern and upscale environment. Inviting atmosphere. One of the best sushi options in old town. Our server was also outstanding! He welcomed us, walked us through the menu and gave recommendations. Food and drinks were excellent and we will be back again soon.
My date was hot. Great service too
Good for bisness lunc.

Great ambience and service.  We tried 4 different sushi rolls, fish was fresh.  Our favorite rolls were the maki rolls and surprisingly, least favorite was one of their more expensive specialty rolls.  Great sushi in the old town area.
So-so. Tai boys don't seems like Japanese
Good food good environment. The sushis are fresh.

Very nice setting. Swift and attentive service. Amazing oysters and lovely sake selection. The rolls were delicious and the wasabi fresh.  Might be the best jack mackerel I've had so far. GF friendly. Worth stopping in.
One of my favorite sushi places.  Great food and service.
Always fresh tasting and exactly what I want out of sushi
Love the food here!
The food and drinks are reasonably priced and very good. We saw the Batsu show and had a great time. For a show and dinner it was all worth it.

Consistently excellent high grade sashimi so I usually order their raw salmon sashimi and cooked home made brown or black rice to the side because I prefer ancient grains.  Definitely come here for lunch to take advantage of their reduced prices for bento, ramen and sashimi boxes.  One time I ordered my normal favorite dish without being presented with their lunch hour menu so if you get here before 3:30 PM take advantage of it and ask to see their bento box options which are cheaper and extremely tasty.   Mist maki here is quite pricey but appears to be incredibly beautiful so I'm definitely going to try something special soon. I love dining outside here for lunch or early dinner and the sashimi here is some of the freshest in the city of Chicago.   The service here is all over the place...sometimes it's quite slow depending on how busy they are.  Because the fish here is so fresh I'm a regular customer an and not many sushi restaurants here in the city will have cooked brown rice so I'm grateful for these more healthful options.

Friendly owner and staffs. We arrived 30 mins before the kitchen closes and they were very welcoming. Better quality sushi than I was expecting. I respect the sushi chef/owner not cut corners to save money like many Japanese restaurants in the Mid West. They had a nice selection of cocktails, beers, sake (it is 'sakeh', not saki), and more.
Amazing food

Excellent

Never disappoints. Solid sushi, fresh, friendly service, nice looking space, NOT noisy unlike so many other restaurants.
Great atmosphere and reasonably priced sushi rolls.
Such great food. Great service.
Coming from San Diego, the bar is set high for sushi, which checks out here! Prices are a bit high and the service is quite slow, even during down hours.

Wow - outstanding Asked Kamehachi to cater a small dinner party with some old friends and I have to give it Michelin 3 stars.  Guests, who were also Japanese, gave it  Michelin 3 Hoshi! I highly recommend - quality was A+, presentation A+ ... an aesthetic feast for all. Special shout out to the delivery guys - did not let technical malfunction of the condo call box stop them - still not quite sure how they accomplished this.

Went in for lunch. Wasn't crowded on a weekday. Service was fast and good. Parking in the neighborhood is difficult.  I had chirashi with brown rice and shishito peppers as a side. It was all really good. I like that they offer brown rice. I don't see it too often in sushi restaurants.

Some of the freshest sushi in town. Always get the fatty tuna. Thank me later.
Good food....excellent drinks 😀

Extremely slow service ...

Food is delicious. Service is horrible! Hostess left my date and I waiting at the bar and forgot about us despite us asking 3 times if the table was ready. Had a reservation for 7 and didn't get seated until 745. Waitress spilt my soup and didn't even come back to clean it up and didn't offer a fresh one. Slow to get around to check on drinks or to bring drinks.  The food was good so I went back a week later. Service was just as terrible. Easily a 5 star place with improved service.
Best sushi in Chicago! Hands down! Thank you Kamehachi for your outstanding service.
Decent sushi place
BATSU! was a great and fun experience. If you are interested in a random, yet entertaining improv experience, this is for you.
Went in for a late light snack. Sushi was delicious,service friendly and efficient. Who could ask for more?

This post if for upstairs theater BATSU. If you like seeing sneaky ninjas topping sake glasses of unsuspecting patrons, standard improv comedy, and bad jokes being punished, all while noming maki rolls, then you’ll probably like BATSU I was pleased with the quality of performances and host, I would recommend this show for birthdays, date nights, bachelorette parties, or pretty much anything else. Planning to be back with a group of people

Place looked good so we went in. It does have good interiors. But the food was a huge letdown. My wife got Salmon sushi. The salmon in the sushi was like leftover baked sushi from another entree. I got the  Nabeyaki udon. The chicken in it was smelly old chicken

Good tasting sushi with relaxed atmosphere, the wait for food was long though even though there were very few patrons. I have been to other sushi places and it does not take nearly a half hour to get three small rolls.
Wonderful food. Great service. Nice atmosphere. We celebrated a birthday and it was perfect!

Expensive for what you get. Sushi is rolled pretty big, though. A little fancier than I was expecting and service took a long time because the waitress was so busy. Lastly, a lady was walking around with a dog while people were eating. May be okay for some, but that's not my jam.

I have gone here about 5 times and have never been disappointed. I had the spicy tuna roll, the salmon deluxe, and a regular California roll. The pieces are fairly large for sushi and I ended up having extra for lunch the next day. I also had the miso soup which is one of the best. Highly recommended
Solid food, nice space.  Enjoyed it and will be back.
Best sushi in Chicago, period.
Great place..

Our server Lauren was so kind and attentive, as we're the server assistants. The chicken teriyaki was delicious!

Regarded as Chicago's first sushi bar ever it now has lots of competition as a result this location has actually moved across the street and redecorated and it's more of a modern Sushi concept. But don't expect any wacky or crazy Sushi Adventures here.  Is Sushi is good as are the other appetizers and entrees but always executed very very well and straightforward. But this restaurant which is now a chain as they have other locations throughout Chicago will do fine and we'll be here forever I'm sure.

This place might actually be too authentic for my taste. I found the Tempura in my Udon Tempura to be tasteless and I didn't care for the broth with the noodles. Nice atmosphere, although it became quite crowded and noisy as three evening want on. My husband enjoyed his sushi.
Bad value

This review is for their Batsu show: One of the best times to be had in Chicago! Everyone from the chefs, restaurant staff, to show staff are amazing. The place, the food, the atmosphere, the music (kudos to you, wonderful music selection), the bar (drinks are DE-LISH!) and of course THE SHOW - LOVE! ♥ Will be bringing anyone who comes visit from now on - and I'll for sure be back soon!
My first time at the new location. Food is just as good as is always was.
Staff is friendly, and my server Lauren was the best!  So kind and accommodating to my young son and I.  Fresh sushi, hot apps, delicious cocktails, and good atmosphere.
Home of Batsu. Check out the best show in town and eat amazing food from Kamechachi.
Amazing place and awesome people! The food was great and the drinks were excellent! Thank you Roger, Jonathan, Mr Kim and the whole staff for the stellar service and great time!
Awesome Maki rolls
Great food, good service!
Love the ramen here, meghan is so nice :-)

Amazing “Rock Shrimp” appetizer. Summer roll is amazing. Blazing Red Dragon Roll is great. The space is about 20 table and has a good wine selection. Cool spot in Old Town. Friendly service! Great dessert and they have an upstairs lounge with events!

Came here this past weekend around 9pm for dinner. Service was slow and inattentive and the rolls were nothing to write home about. Overall had a very average experience, I probably won't be back. It's also in a very noisy area so I wouldn't recommend for a date.

Once again,  a great time and great food.

The bar has a great atmosphere! Lighting, sound and decor create a very relaxed vibe along with a very friendly staff - it's a great place to have a drink after work! The reason I gave this place a 4 instead of 5 is because I tend to judge a true sushi place for their sashimi. I grew up on the coast and have ate a fair amount of sashimi in my lifetime. I ordered the white tuna, red tuna, Walu and salmon and the presentation was beautiful. But I would have to say that it was just sub-par sashimi and the taste and size did not match the price point. Could not have been Grade 1 but you pay grade 1prices. Some might say it's because you're in old town! But being a resident of old town if I'm going to pay the price I still want the quality! Maybe I ordered the wrong item but I believe sashimi is something you just can't mess up! I will probably return for the atmosphere but will not be ordering the sashimi.
Fresh sushi, excellent roll options, cool atmosphere, good service, one of my favorite restaurants to visit in Lincoln Park. Don't forget the sake!

I think this place has awful service, our waitress was the worst I have ever seen. The sushi was just okay nothing to rave about at all. What a shame and disappointment.  The restaurant it self was well put together decrovtived very nicely.
Outstanding sushi. Wide fresh selection. Well presented.

This is one of my favorite sushi restaurants in town. The move from their old location gave them the chance to create an even more upscale feeling restaurant. It's a bit small inside but the fish has always tasted fresh and I've enjoyed every meal. The portions are generous and tasty.  It's a great place for a date night or going out with friends. I'd even bring clients here as well. You can't go wrong with Kamehachi!
Enjoyed the food (ordered the salmon teryaki and also an order of sushi). Dark, quiet place which makes it good for a romantic dinner. Great location.
Great food and drinks
Best udon noodles I've ever had! The broth was superb! The scallop appetizer was so good. Great service! Cozy atmosphere.
Always top notch service and the food is always fulfilling

Delicious maki at a decent price - the space is gorgeously decorated and laid out well. I can hear the music AND my conversation- a lot of places it's one or the other. Service was great and fairly quick. Granted, I got here right when they opened for lunch, but I'd love to come back for dinner and see what they have in store!
our go-to sushi spot. spicy edamame is a must! their signature maki rolls are the best in the city!

The nigiri is not fresh and is served warm as if it was not stored well. The Hotate and kampachi nigiri had a really bitter aftertaste (not stored well maybe?). Over all the food quality does not reflect on the prices.
Great food, very quick service. Ambience is quite classy. Crazy Chicago rolls are a must.
If we lived closer, we would be regulars. Classic french preparation with great ingredients. Service was over-the-top!
They sat us by the waiting couches against our request and the uncooked food took almost an hour to come.....

I never knew I liked the Japanese cuisine this much, but Kamehachi made me love it. The salmon was phenomenal and the Japanese beer just great. The service is very good and the prices are not bad for the quality
Great sushi and saki. Go here if you're visiting Chicago and want some sushi.

Their sushi is always great, but we were here for there for the Batsu! Show which was hilarious and fun for a date or a group. It's basically an improv competition show (Like "Who's Line is it Anyway") with punishment for the losers.
Great sushi, service could use a little help.
Atmosphere was great, just wished the food portions were bigger.
Wow! Great sushi!
Great sushi nice bar
very good
Great service and excellent food. Worth a visit.

One of my favorite sushi places in Chicago! A MUST try is the Green Turtle roll, absolutely the best roll I have EVER eaten! Service is always good, but expect a wait on weekend evenings. Reservations are recommended. For two people with appetizers and a glass of wine each, expect about $150-$170 with tip and tax.
I've only come here for Batsu, the show upstairs on Thursdays and Fridays at 8pm- but the food was amazing and I had a great time!
Top quality Japanese food. High level of service at every interaction.  A gem.  Teriyaki salmon and Sukiyaki soup are 2 standouts.
Don't go there....poor service, small portions, unreasonable expensive.......
Great Japanese for years !!
Great rolls and sushi.
Excellent sushi spot with a stylish atmosphere.
Good sushi but the other locations to the north is better
Pretty good sushi. Would go here again if someone else in the group wanted to, but wouldn't be my top pick for sushi in Chicago.
Pretty good sushi.  Not particularly memorable.  The sake selection was good and the price was reasonable.

Possibly the best Japanese in America, but definitely in Chicago by light years.  It is truly Sushi grade fish unlike most places that have no business serving sushi and sashimi.  There are also regular high quality sashimi like the Tasmanian salmon being my favorite.  The katsu is also fantastic and authentically prepared.  It is a restaurant that actually can stand on its food instead of just gouging alcoholics out for "dinner" instead.
Mediocre quality and anemic sushi (fish to rice proportions are quite unusual). They do have a diverse sake selection and friendly service.

I've been here a few times and really enjoyed it, however my last experience was really sub par. The fish did not taste fresh at all and the rolls were just okay. With the old town price tag, I think the food should always be consistent.

Appetizers are fine and you can't beat the location but I was really disappointed with the quality of fish they use in the sushi.  It's one thing to get mediocre quality and pay $7 per roll but the high Old Town prices don't match the quality of the sushi.
Nice place for traditional Japanese food. The service was friendly and the food was great but in small portions. The dishes were a little expensive but it's a nice place to visit once in a while.

Nice spot on Wells street! Flavors taste authentic-- especially in the special sushi garnishes and delicate combinations. I can really appreciate the chefs' attention to detail. Definitely will be going back.

Anywhere that uses real crab in their CA rolls holds a special place in my heart. Regulars/Friends took us here and I was pleasantly surprised at the amazing quality for what qualifies as affordable sushi in my book. The sunset and summer (or was it called sunrise?) rolls were my favorite. Food presentation and decor were both simple and beautiful. I felt like I was eating inside the field house of a Japanese garden. My cocktails were delicious and our waitress was also very sweet. Not a single complaint from a usually pretty picky girl. I can't wait to show this place off to someone else.
EXCELLENT sushi with great service. Highly recommend to anybody!

One of my favorite sushi places in the city. It is very nice and trendy environment! The sushi rolls are great- tuna and salmon rolls are among some of my favorite. As an appetizer, I would recommend the edamame beans!
The room design is really fancy! I like it so much and I am a huge fan for this restaurant. The tuna rolll and unagi roll is tasty and fresh. I will definity come again with my friends and family .
The sushi was really good. It is not over priced at all and we loved the environment. It is such a nice spot.
The best on planet Earth!
Great sushi good variety. Many locations and a great wait staff.

The sushi at Kamehachi is very fresh and I've always had very positive, friendly experiences there. If you're looking for a sushi place where you can get a roll with cooked salmon, this will be your new go-to.
Kamehaci staff is always great! Service is fantastic too! Always have a great time being there. Even the take out food stays fresh and delicious!

Was a great place for dinner.  Call and make reservations or you might be waiting for a table.  Table is outside is nice but prefer the bar or table.  Service was attentive up until food was served.  Food here is great and its better to order and share as everything is served on large plates.
I've been going here sine I was a kid. The vast menu allows for you to try never try the same thing twice, and you will still never be dissapointed. Great service, location, and of course, sushi.

DO NOT GO! My girlfriend and I received food poisoning from Kamehachi in Old Town. She ate the Chicken Teriyaki (with a house salad) that I had a bit of, and I had a Tuna D'Lux D'Lux roll with miso soup and spicy edamame. We didn't do anything else the entire night. The next day we woke up and both felt like we had been hit by a truck. She was violently vomiting, severely dehydrated (her brother, a physician, gave her an IV), feverish, and dizzy. If it wasn't for her being a nurse and her brother being a physician, we would have taken her to the ER. I had similar, but not as severe, side effects from the food. My guess is it was the chicken teriyaki. When I spoke with the manager, Lateef, he told me to have her brother, the doctor, call him that night and explain the symptoms. When he called 10-15 minutes later, Lateef had left. The doctor explained that this must have been food poisoning and all the symptoms that were related all led him to believe that it came from Kamehachi. I called in today and Lateef explained that he needs to obtain a stool sample before they can do anything about it (they also wouldn't contact the doctor and said he would have to contact them if anything was to be done). The service, while there, was good, decor was great, but the management and food are far below average. Will be reporting them elsewhere as well. AGAIN, BE WARNED! THIS COULD HAVE BEEN MUCH MORE SEVERE IF SHE WASN'T IN THE CARE OF A DOCTOR AT HOME!!
Awesome miso soup, and great sushi! Service was good aside from the place being a bit small it's good.
Good sushi. Nice waitresses. The complete dinner with the salad and soup leaves me satiated.
Delicious sushi and a beautiful establishment.  Great place to take someone from out of town or an a really nice date.  Bit pricey though since it is a nice place.
